# Incident Analytics + Reporting

Add operational reporting and analytics on top of the runtime-verified incident lifecycle. All additive — no schema changes, no modifications to existing incident submission/review flow.

## Proposed Changes

---

### Backend Analytics

#### [NEW] [incidentAnalyticsRoutes.js](file:///c:/dev/sams-platform/backend/routes/incidentAnalyticsRoutes.js)

All endpoints use [authenticateToken](file:///c:/dev/sams-platform/backend/middleware/auth.js#29-55), support optional query filters (`dateFrom`, `dateTo`, `status`, `severity`, `category`, `incidentType`, `driverId`, `vehicleId`), and aggregate in SQL.

**Endpoints:**

| Endpoint | Returns |
|---|---|
| `GET /analytics/summary` | KPI counts (total, open, under review, resolved, dismissed), avg resolution time, counts by severity/category/type |
| `GET /analytics/trends` | Time-series: incidents per day/week/month, groupable by severity/category/status/type |
| `GET /analytics/by-driver` | Ranked driver list: incident count, open count, severity-weighted score. Uses snapshot `driverName` as fallback |
| `GET /analytics/by-vehicle` | Vehicle breakdown: incident count, open count, by-category. Uses `vehicleLabel` as fallback |
| `GET /analytics/aging` | Age buckets (0-1d, 2-7d, 8-30d, 31+d) for open + under-review incidents |
| `GET /analytics/export` | CSV stream of filtered incidents with snapshot-safe fields |

All queries use `Incident.findAll()` with `where` clauses, `sequelize.fn('COUNT')`, `sequelize.fn('DATE')`, and `GROUP BY`. No raw SQL needed for portability.

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///c:/dev/sams-platform/backend/server.js)

Mount analytics routes under existing incident route namespace:
```js
apiRouter.use('/incidents', require('./routes/incidentAnalyticsRoutes'));
```

